Tired of creating the input files for make.contigs? Let mothur do that for you! The make.file command takes a input directory and creates a file containing the fastq or gz files in the directory.

__TOC__

==Default Settings==
The make.fastq command parameters are inputdir and type.  Inputdir is required.

 mothur > make.file(inputdir=fastqTest)

The resulting fileList.paired.file looks like:

