 ...

===numcols===
The numcols parameter allows you to set number of columns you mothur to make in the file.  Options 2 or 3. Default=3, meaning groupName forwardFastq reverseFastq. The groupName is made from the beginning part of the forwardFastq file. Everything up to the first '' or if no '' is found then the root of the forwardFastq filename. 

===prefix===
The prefix parameter allows you to enter your own prefix for the output filename. Default=stability.

  mothur > make.file(inputdir=gzTest, type=gz, prefix=myReallyAwesomeData)

Would create a file containing the list of gz files in gzTest named myReallyAwesomeData.files.

